(40, 24, 50, 40, 24, 42, 44, 'in a day when he looketh not for him', 'Readiness for the Lord''s Return', 'Both passages emphasize the unexpected timing of the Lord''s coming. They highlight the need for vigilance and readiness, as the arrival will occur when one is not aware.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 50, 20, 29, 1, 1, NULL, 'Sudden Destruction and Unawareness', 'This connection highlights the theme of unexpected judgment. Both passages emphasize the suddenness of destruction for those unprepared or unresponsive.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 51, 40, 8, 12, 12, 'there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth', 'Weeping and Gnashing of Teeth', 'Both passages emphasize the consequence of exclusion from the kingdom, highlighting a fate of suffering. The phrase ''weeping and gnashing of teeth'' serves as a vivid description of this punishment in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 51, 42, 12, 46, 46, 'cut him asunder', 'Servant Punishment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the punishment of a servant who is unprepared for his master''s return. They share the phrase ''cut him asunder'' and describe the fate of being appointed with the hypocrites or unbelievers, highlighting a theme of judgment.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 51, 40, 22, 13, 13, 'there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth', 'Weeping and Gnashing of Teeth', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of unfaithfulness, culminating in punishment described as ''weeping and gnashing of teeth.'' This connection highlights a theme of judgment for those deemed unworthy.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 51, 18, 20, 29, 29, 'his portion with the hypocrites', 'Wickedness and Divine Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the fate of the wicked as determined by God. Matthew 24:51 speaks of a portion with the hypocrites, while Job 20:29 describes the portion of a wicked man from God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 51, 23, 33, 14, 14, 'hypocrites', 'Judgment of the Hypocrites', 'Both passages emphasize the fate of hypocrites, depicting fear and punishment. Matthew speaks of being cut asunder and assigned to the hypocrites, while Isaiah describes fearfulness among hypocrites facing devouring fire.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 51, 42, 13, 28, 28, 'weeping and gnashing of teeth', 'Weeping and Gnashing of Teeth', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''weeping and gnashing of teeth,'' indicating a state of regret and exclusion from the kingdom of God. This connection highlights the consequences of being unfaithful or hypocritical.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 1, 42, 12, 35, 36, 'to meet the bridegroom', 'Waiting for the Bridegroom', 'Both passages emphasize the readiness of those waiting for the bridegroom or lord. They highlight the importance of being prepared with lamps burning and being alert for the return.', 'theme', 0.748, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 1, 40, 24, 42, 51, 'meet the bridegroom', 'Readiness for the Lord''s Coming', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of being prepared for the unexpected arrival of the Lord. The ten virgins in Matthew 25:1 are waiting for the bridegroom, paralleling the call to watchfulness in Matthew 24:42-51.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 1, 50, 2, 15, 16, NULL, 'Light and Preparedness Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of being prepared and shining as lights. The ten virgins are called to be ready for the bridegroom, while Philippians emphasizes shining as lights in a perverse nation.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 1, 66, 19, 7, 7, 'bridegroom', 'Marriage and Readiness Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of preparation for a wedding. Both passages emphasize the importance of being ready to meet the bridegroom, reflecting the anticipation of the marriage of the Lamb.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 1, 66, 21, 9, 9, 'bridegroom', 'Connection of Bride and Bridegroom', 'This connection highlights the theme of the bride and bridegroom, where the ten virgins await the bridegroom in Matthew, paralleling the depiction of the bride, the Lamb's wife, in Revelation. Both passages emphasize the anticipation and readiness for the coming of the bridegroom.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 1, 23, 54, 5, 5, 'bridegroom', 'Marriage Imagery in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of God as a bridegroom and the faithful as brides. Both passages emphasize the relationship between the divine and the faithful, with the bridegroom in Matthew and the husband in Isaiah.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 1, 40, 13, 24, 24, NULL, 'Parables of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the nature of the kingdom of heaven through parables. They illustrate different aspects of readiness and the consequences of one''s actions within that kingdom.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 2, 24, 24, 2, 2, NULL, 'Wisdom and Foolishness in Judgment', 'This connection highlights the distinction between the wise and foolish in Matthew and the good and bad figs in Jeremiah. Both passages emphasize a judgment based on the quality of the subjects, whether they are wise or foolish, good or bad.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 2, 46, 10, 1, 5, 'And five of them were wise', 'Wisdom and Foolishness in Faith', 'This connection highlights the distinction between the wise and foolish in faith. Both passages emphasize the consequences of one''s choices, with the wise being prepared and the foolish facing judgment.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 2, 40, 13, 19, 23, 'five were foolish', 'Wisdom and Understanding in Parables', 'This connection highlights the distinction between the wise and foolish in their understanding of the word. Both passages emphasize the importance of comprehension and the consequences of failing to grasp the message.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 2, 40, 13, 47, 48, NULL, 'Wisdom and Judgment in Parables', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the wise and foolish or good and bad. The wise in Matthew 25:2 are akin to the good gathered in Matthew 13:48, highlighting a theme of discernment in the kingdom of heaven.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 2, 65, 1, 5, 5, NULL, 'Wisdom and Belief in Judgment', 'This connection highlights the distinction between the wise and foolish in Matthew and the fate of those who did not believe in Jude. Both passages emphasize the consequences of one''s actions and beliefs, particularly in the context of judgment.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 2, 62, 2, 19, 19, 'five were foolish', 'Wisdom and Belonging', 'This connection highlights the distinction between the wise and foolish, paralleling the idea of true belonging versus false association. Both passages emphasize the importance of genuine faith and the consequences of not being part of the faithful community.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 3, 66, 3, 15, 16, NULL, 'Preparedness and Spiritual State', 'This connection highlights the theme of readiness and the consequences of being unprepared. Both passages emphasize the importance of being fully equipped, whether with oil for lamps or being spiritually hot or cold.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 3, 55, 3, 5, 5, 'took no oil with them', 'Foolishness and Godliness Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrast between those who are unprepared, as seen in the foolish virgins who took no oil, and those who exhibit a superficial form of godliness without true power. Both passages emphasize the importance of genuine readiness and spiritual substance.', 'theme', 0.37, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 3, 23, 48, 1, 2, 'foolish', 'Foolishness and Lack of Truth', 'This connection highlights the theme of foolishness in both passages. The ''foolish'' in Matthew 25:3 reflects a lack of preparation and truthfulness, paralleling Isaiah 48:1-2''s depiction of those who swear by the Lord but do not do so in truth or righteousness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 3, 23, 58, 2, 2, 'took no oil with them', 'Preparedness and Seeking God', 'This connection highlights the importance of being prepared in faith. Both passages emphasize the necessity of having what is needed to approach God, whether it be oil for lamps or seeking His ordinances.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 3, 66, 3, 1, 1, 'took no oil with them', 'Preparedness and Spiritual Vigilance', 'This connection highlights the theme of being prepared spiritually. In Matthew, the foolish took no oil, symbolizing a lack of readiness, while in Revelation, the church in Sardis is warned about being dead despite having a name that suggests life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 3, 58, 12, 15, 15, NULL, 'Preparedness and Spiritual Vigilance', 'This connection highlights the importance of being prepared and vigilant in one''s faith. Both passages emphasize the consequences of neglecting spiritual readiness, as seen in the foolishness of taking no oil and the warning against failing to uphold grace.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 3, 40, 23, 25, 26, NULL, 'Foolishness and Inner Purity', 'This connection highlights the theme of inner versus outer purity. Both passages emphasize the importance of what is within, contrasting the foolishness of neglecting inner preparation with the hypocrisy of focusing solely on outward appearances.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 4, 45, 8, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Preparedness and Spirit', 'This connection highlights the importance of being prepared spiritually, as the wise took oil for their lamps, symbolizing readiness. Similarly, Romans emphasizes the necessity of having the Spirit of God dwell within, indicating spiritual preparedness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 4, 62, 2, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Wisdom and Anointing', 'This connection highlights the importance of being prepared and having the necessary resources for spiritual readiness. Both passages emphasize the idea of abiding in a state of preparedness, whether through the wise taking oil or the anointing that teaches and abides in believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
